UserOptionDefinition.Device_Nevada_Spawner_V2_C.On Player Ent: A player enters the spawned vehicle
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Nevada_Spawner_V2_C.On Player Exi: A player exits the spawned vehicle
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Nevada_Spawner_V2_C.On Vehicle Sp: A vehicle is spawned or respawned.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Nevada_Spawner_V2_C.Apply OffRoad: Apply off-road tires to the vehicle if the vehicle can receive them.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Nevada_Spawner_V2_C.Vehicle Healt: Determines how much damage the vehicle can take before destruction.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Nevada_Spawner_V2_C.Vehicle Indes: Determines if the Vehicle can be destroyed by damage.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Nevada_Spawner_V2_C.Destroy when: Determines if the Vehicle will destroy itself when stuck underwater.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Nevada_Spawner_V2_C.EnableRespawn: Determines if the Vehicle will respawn after being destroyed.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Nevada_Spawner_V2_C.bEnableCannon: Determines if the cannon can be used.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Nevada_Spawner_V2_C.bEnableTracto: Determines if the tractor beam is enabled.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Nevada_Spawner_V2_C.Enabled Durin: Determines the game phases during which the device will be enabled. If set to CREATE ONLY, will only be enabled while editing your Island.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Nevada_Spawner_V2_C.RebootBehavio: Determines whether or not the UFO can reboot, and how many times.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Nevada_Spawner_V2_C.Visible Durin: Determines whether the device is visible during the game. This does affect its collision properties.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Nevada_Spawner_V2_C.Disable.Descr: Disable the Vehicle Spawner, stopping it from spawning any more vehicles.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Nevada_Spawner_V2_C.Enable.Descri: Enable the Vehicle Spawner, allowing it to spawn vehicles.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Nevada_Spawner_V2_C.Allowed Class: If set to All, All Classes (including players with NO CLASS) are affected. Otherwise, the chosen Class will be used to determine the Affects Class effect. ANY CLASS - Players with a Class assigned, regardless of what Class it is. NO CLASS - Players without any assigned class.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Nevada_Spawner_V2_C.Destroy Vehic: If the vehicle that this spawner created still exists, destroy it.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Nevada_Spawner_V2_C.Reboots.Descr: Number of times this UFO can reboot to full health after it is reduced to zero health.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Nevada_Spawner_V2_C.Destroy Vehic: ON will destroy an already spawned vehicle when this spawner is disabled.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Nevada_Spawner_V2_C.Pop All Tires: Pop all of the tires on the vehicle, if the vehicle has tires to pop.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Nevada_Spawner_V2_C.Repair All Ti: Repair all of the tires on the vehicle, if the vehicle has tires to repair.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Nevada_Spawner_V2_C.Repair Vehicl: Restore the spawned vehicle to full health.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Nevada_Spawner_V2_C.Remove Tire M: Revert to road tires on the vehicle if the vehicle can receive them.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Nevada_Spawner_V2_C.Assigns Drive: Seats the player that instigated the message as the spawned vehicle's driver.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Nevada_Spawner_V2_C.Respawn Vehic: Spawns the vehicle (Destroying the existing vehicle if it still exists).
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Nevada_Spawner_V2_C.Activating Te: The Team this device belongs to.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Nevada_Spawner_V2_C.Water Destruc: When the vehicle becomes too deep in water to drive, destroy it after this delay.
When the vehicle is destroyed, respawn it after this delay. (The first vehicle spawned does not use this delay.)
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Nevada_Spawner_V2_C.Respawn Vehic: YES will spawn a vehicle when the device is enabled. ONLY IF NEEDED will not reset an existing vehicle.
